# room-connect — Project Overview

room-connect is an **interactive 3D volume connectivity editor**. It lets users load, visualise, and edit connectivity graphs embedded in 3D volumetric data (e.g. architectural room layouts, cellular networks, cave systems). Connectivity is represented as a graph whose nodes are volumetric regions and whose edges encode adjacency or passage relationships.

## High-level goals

1. Load volumetric data from standard formats (NumPy `.npy`, NIfTI, HDF5).
2. Render interactive 3D visualisations of the volume and its connectivity graph.
3. Allow users to add, remove, and re-label nodes and edges through both a GUI and a Python API.
4. Export the edited connectivity graph and annotated volume to standard formats.

## Repository layout

```
room-connect/
├── src/room_connect/       # Installable Python package (src layout)
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── graph.py            # Connectivity graph data model
│   ├── volume.py           # Volume loading / processing utilities
│   ├── editor.py           # High-level editor API
│   └── viz/                # Visualisation back-ends
│       ├── __init__.py
│       └── renderer.py
├── tests/                  # pytest test suite
├── docs/                   # Documentation source (MkDocs)
├── pyproject.toml          # Project metadata and build config
└── README.md
```

## Development workflow

- Install in editable mode: `pip install -e ".[dev]"`
- Run tests: `pytest`
- Lint / format: `ruff check . && ruff format .`
- Type-check: `mypy src`
